1. e4 { The Opera Game: Morphy plays a casual game against two amateur
allies during a night at the opera, and turns it into the most famous
miniature in chess history. } e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 Bg4 { A dubious pin.
Black should prefer 3...exd4 or 3...Nf6, developing a piece instead of
attacking one that can simply move away with tempo. } (3... exd4 4. Nxd4
Nf6 5. Nc3 { and Black has a normal, slightly passive but solid
position. }) 4. dxe5 Bxf3 5. Qxf3 dxe5 6. Bc4 Nf6 7. Qb3 { Double
attack on b7 and f7. } Qe7 8. Nc3 { Morphy calmly develops instead of
grabbing the pawn immediately, since 8. Qxb7 Qb4+ trades queens into an
equal ending. } c6 9. Bg5 b5 10. Nxb5 cxb5 11. Bxb5+ Nbd7 12. O-O-O Rd8
13. Rxd7 Rxd7 14. Rd1 Qe6 15. Bxd7+ Nxd7 16. Qb8+ Nxb8 17. Rd8# 1-0
